# Divine Domains																																			
Death Domain	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Cleric Class Feature.Divine Domain.SpecialQuality.Class Feature		DESC:The Death domain is concerned with the forces that cause death, as well as the negative energy that gives rise to undead creatures. Deities such as Chemosh, Myrkul, and WeeJas are patrons of necromancers, death knights, liches, mummy lords, and vampires. Gods of the Death domain also embody murder (Anubi . Bhaal, and Pyremius), pain (Iuz or Loviatar), disease or poison (Incabulos, Talona, or Morgion), and the underworld (Hades and He!).	KEY:Divine Domain ~ Death Domain	PREALIGN:LE,NE,CE								BONUS:VAR|POOL_Cleric_Cantrip|3+(ClericLVL>=4)+(ClericLVL>=10)									ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Death Domain ~ Bonus Proficiency|PREVARGTEQ:ClericLVL,1	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Death Domain ~ Reaper|PREVARGTEQ:ClericLVL,1	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Channel Divinity ~ Touch of Death|PREVARGTEQ:ClericLVL,2	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Death Domain ~ Inescapable Destruction|PREVARGTEQ:ClericLVL,6	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Death Domain ~ Divine Strike|PREVARGTEQ:ClericLVL,8	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Death Domain ~ Improved Reaper|PREVARGTEQ:ClericLVL,17	SPELLLEVEL:DOMAIN|Death Domain=1|False Life,Ray of Sickness|Death Domain=3|Blindness/Deafness,Ray of Enfeeblement|Death Domain=5|Animate Dead,Vampiric Touch|Death Domain=7|Blight,Death Ward|Death Domain=9|Antilife Shell,Cloudkill			SOURCEPAGE:DMG			
																																			
# Death Domain																																			
Bonus Proficiency	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Cleric Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Class Feature		DESC:When the cleric chooses this domain at 1st level, he or she gains proficiency with martial weapons.	KEY:Death Domain ~ Bonus Proficiency																		ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|TYPE=WeaponProfMartial									SOURCEPAGE:DMG			
Reaper	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Cleric Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Class Feature		DESC:At 1st level, the cleric learns one necromancy cantrip of his or her choice from any spell list. When the cleric casts a necromancy cantrip that normally targets only one creature, the spell can instead target two creatures within range and within 5 feet of each other.	KEY:Death Domain ~ Reaper				DEFINE:POOL_Cleric_Necromancy_Cantrip|0					BONUS:VAR|POOL_Cleric_Necromancy_Cantrip|1																		SOURCEPAGE:DMG			
Channel Divinity: Touch of Death	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Cleric Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Class Feature		DESC::Starting at 2nd level, the cleric can use Channel Divinity to destroy another creature's life force by touch. When the cleric hits a creature with a melee attack, the cleric can use Channel Divinity to deal extra necrotic damage to the target. The damage equals 5 + twice his or her cleric level.	KEY:Channel Divinity ~ Touch of Death																											SOURCEPAGE:DMG			
Inescapable Destruction	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Cleric Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Class Feature		DESC:Starting at 6th level, the cleric's ability to channel negative energy becomes more potent. Necrotic damage dealt by the character's cleric spells and Channel Divinity options ignores resistance to necrotic damage.	KEY:Death Domain ~ Inescapable Destruction																											SOURCEPAGE:DMG			
Divine Strike	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Cleric Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Class Feature		DESC:At 8th level, you gain the ability to infuse your weapon strikes with divine energy. Once on each of your turns when you hit a creature with a weapon attack, you can cause the attack to deal an extra %1d8 necrotic damage to the target.|((ClericLVL>=8)+(ClericLVL>=14))	KEY:Death Domain ~ Divine Strike																											SOURCEPAGE:DMG			
Improved Reaper	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Cleric Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Class Feature		DESC::Starting at 17th level, when the cleric casts a necromancy spell of 1st through 5th level that targets only one creature, the spell can instead target two creatures within range and within 5 feet of each other. If the spell consumes its material components, the cleric must provide them for each target.	KEY:Death Domain ~ Improved Reaper																											SOURCEPAGE:DMG			
																																			
#Necromancy cantrip																																			
Chill Touch	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Cleric Necromancy Cantrip		DESC:You create a ghostly, skeletal hand in the space o f a creature within range. Make a ranged spell attack against the creature to assail it with the chill o f the grave. On a hit, the target takes 1d8 necrotic damage, and it can’t regain hit points until the start o f your next turn. Until then, the hand clings to the target. If you hit an undead target, it also has disadvantage on attack rolls against you until the end o f your next turn. This spell’s damage increases by 1d8 when you reach 5th level (2d8), 11th level (3d8), and 17th level (4d8).	KEY:Cleric Necromancy Cantrip ~ Chill Touch																		SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Cleric=0|Chill Touch									SOURCEPAGE:DMG			
Spare the Dying	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Cleric Necromancy Cantrip		DESC:You touch a living creature that has 0 hit points. The creature becomes stable. This spell has no effect on undead or constructs.	KEY:Cleric Necromancy Cantrip ~ Spare the Dying																		SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Cleric=0|Spare the Dying									SOURCEPAGE:DMG			
																																			
### Sacred Oaths																																			
Oathbreaker	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Class Feature.Sacred Oath		DESC:.An Oathbreaker is a paladin who breaks his or her sacred oaths to pursue some dark ambition or serve an evil power. Whatever light burned in the paladin's heart has been extinguished. Only darkness remains.	KEY:Sacred Oath ~ Oathbreaker	PREALIGN:LE,NE,CE																	ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Channel Divinity ~ Control Undead|PRECLASS:1,Paladin=3	ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Channel Divinity ~ Dreadful Aspect|PRECLASS:1,Paladin=3	ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Oathbreaker ~ Aura Of Hate|PRECLASS:1,Paladin=7	ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Oathbreaker ~ Supernatural Resistance|PRECLASS:1,Paladin=15	ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Oathbreaker ~ Dread Lord|PRECLASS:1,Paladin=20		SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Paladin=1|Hellish Rebuke,Inflict Wounds|PRECLASS:1,Paladin=3	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Paladin=2|Crown of Madness,Darkness|PRECLASS:1,Paladin=5	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Paladin=3|Animate Dead,Bestow curse|PRECLASS:1,Paladin=9	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Paladin=4|Blight,Confusion|PRECLASS:1,Paladin=13	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Paladin=5|Contagion,Dominate Person|PRECLASS:1,Paladin=17	SOURCEPAGE:DMG
																																			
# Oathbreaker																																			
#Channel Divinity	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.SpecialQuality		DESC:An Oathbreaker paladin of 3rd level or higher gains the following two Channel Divinity options.	KEY:Oathbreaker ~ Channel Divinity																											SORTKEY:Class			
Control Undead	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.SpecialQuality		DESC:As an action, the paladin targets one undead creature he or she can see within 30 feet of him or her. The target must make a Wisdom saving throw. On a failed save, the target must obey the paladin's commands for the next 24 hours, or until the paladin uses this Channel Divinity option again. An undead whose challenge rating is equal to or greater than the paladin's level is immune to this effect.	KEY:Channel Divinity ~ Control Undead																											SORTKEY:Class			
Dreadful Aspect	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.SpecialQuality		DESC:As an action, the paladin channels the darkest emotions and focuses them into a burst of magical menace. Each creature of the paladin's choice within 30 feet of the paladin must make a Wisdom saving throw if it can see the paladin. On a failed save, the target is frightened of the paladin for 1 minute. If a creature frightened by this effect ends its turn more than 30 feet away from the paladin, it can attempt another Wisdom saving throw to end the effect on it.	KEY:Channel Divinity ~ Dreadful Aspect																											SORTKEY:Class			
Aura Of Hate	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.SpecialQuality		DESC:Starting at 7th level, the paladin, as well any fiends and undead within 10 feet of the paladin, gains a bonus to melee weapon damage rolls equal to the paladin's Charisma modifier (minimum of +1). A creature can benefit from this feature from only one paladin at a time. At 18th level, the range of this aura increases to 30 feet.	KEY:Oathbreaker ~ Aura Of Hate																											SORTKEY:Class			
Supernatural Resistance	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.SpecialQuality		DESC:At 15th level, the paladin gains resistance to bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing damage from nonmagical weapons.	KEY:Oathbreaker ~ Supernatural Resistance																											SORTKEY:Class			
Dread Lord	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.SpecialQuality		DESC:At 20th-level, the paladin can, as an action, surround himself or herself with an aura of gloom that lasts for 1 minute. The aura reduces any bright light in a 30-foot radius around the paladin to dim light. Whenever an enemy that is frightened by the paladin starts its turn in the aura, it takes 4d10 psychic damage. Additionally, the paladin and creatures he or she chooses in the aura are draped in deeper shadow. Creatures that rely on sight have disadvantage on attack rolls against creatures draped in this shadow. While the aura lasts, the paladin can use a bonus action on his or her turn to cause the shadows in the aura to attack one creature. The paladin makes a melee spell attack against the target. If the attack hits, the target takes necrotic damage equal to 3d10 +.the paladin's Charisma modifier. After activating the aura, the paladin can't do so again until he or she finishes a long rest.	KEY:Oathbreaker ~ Dread Lord																											SORTKEY:Class			
